                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d305">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.945/1115: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Woods</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-05-28T17:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 28, 1924—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 28—12:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>126. My number [<hi rend="italic">114</hi>], May 23, 6 p.m.<note n="57"
                        xml:id="d305fn57">Not printed.</note> I understand that the Cabinet at a
                    meeting held this morning approved the draft of <pb facs="0492" n="398"
                        xml:id="pg_398"/> an instruction to Hanihara to “lodge a solemn protest.” An
                    official statement in this connection to be issued this afternoon will be cabled
                    by the Associated Press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woods</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
